I"æ<h2 id="1-what-is-npm-create-an-npm-account">1. What is <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">npm</a>? Create an npm account.</h2>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code> is a package manager for the JavaScript programming language.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code> is the command line client that allows developers to install and publish packages - packaged modules of code.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code> is an <a href="https://github.com/npm">open source</a> project and free to use.</p>

<p>Official website: <strong><a href="https://npmjs.com/">npm</a></strong></p>

<p>Documentation: <strong><a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/">npm Docs</a></strong></p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/npm/1-npm-landing-page.png" alt="NPM Landing Page" /></p>

<p>Create an npm account at: <strong><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/signup">Sign Up</a></strong></p>

<p>Login: <strong><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/login">Login</a></strong></p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/npm/3-npm-sign-up.png" alt="NPM Sign Up" /></p>

<h2 id="2-what-is-nodejs-download-nodejs">2. What is <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">Node.js</a>? Download Node.js.</h2>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Node.js</code> is an open-source, cross-platform, back-end JavaScript runtime environment.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Node.js</code> is an <a href="https://github.com/nodejs">open source</a> project and free to use.</p>

<p>Official website: <strong><a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">Nodejs</a></strong></p>

<p>Documentation: <strong><a href="https://nodejs.org/en/docs/">Nodejs Docs</a></strong></p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/npm/1-nodejs-landing-page.png" alt="NPM Landing Page" /></p>

<p>Download Node.js at: <strong><a href="https://nodejs.org/en/download/">Download Node.js</a></strong></p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/npm/2-nodejs-download.png" alt="Nodejs Download" /></p>

